Scribes could read and write, unlike many people in Egypt. Right below the pharaoh, there were nobles and priests. Nobles could hold government posts. Priests were responsible for pleasing the gods. There were soldiers whom supervised the peasants, farmers, and slraves who were involved in the building of individual structures, pyramids, and palaces. Slaves and farmers were at the bottom of the Egypt social structure. Slaves were exhausted from being put to work by the pharaohs. They were prisoners of war and were forced to put all their work into buildineg projects and more. Farmers tended the fields, raised animals, kept canals, and more. They worked immensely.
